tweet_raw: Made my first cast on warpcast 9 months ago. I never really used it after that because I never had engagement there and most of my audience/friends are on Twitter. But in the last hour or so I got 50ish follows. All from the Twitter folks who didnt use warpcast so far or didnt care (like me).This is probably how mass adoption feels like. Everyone joins in because of frames right marketing better UX experience and builders coming together.The problem will be the DAUs retention rate. Threads from Meta saw the same influx and everyone from Twitter moved there and said they would ditch the Twitter for good. Mfers got back on X in less than 2 weeks.Currently as I understand there are some good ways to ape in or do degen stuff on farcaster but there is also a possibility of losing liquidity like how friendtech did.User retention + liquidity is the main play and one of the biggest challenges for the founders and builders on the farcaster. P.S. I might be 100% wrong. Feel free to comment down anything. Will write a detailed thread later.

tweet_raw: Tether May Be The Best Business In The WorldCritics of the new digital financial system are fond of claiming that blockchain technology has not created any real products. Their view of the world is that crypto enthusiasts are merely trading digital tokens back and forth for speculation but no real problems have been solved to date.This is obviously not true.Bitcoin is an $850 billion asset that has approximately $600 billion being held by long-term holders who are seeking to protect their purchasing power. That alone should negate the critics but they rarely accept that argument as valid for some unknown reason.This opens the door for an even more interesting response — stablecoins have become a killer app of blockchain technology.Let’s use Tether the leading stablecoin as the example. The company has almost $100 billion in various fiat currencies that have been tokenized on different blockchains.That money is held in a variety of investments to ensure the reserves are always available and protected.This approach to a tokenized asset (cash!) has turned Tether into one of the best businesses in the world. Yesterday CEO @paoloardoino published the following statistics about their Q4 performance:- profit for the quarter: $2.85B of which ~$1B in net operational profit (mainly US t-bill interests) ~$1.85B from gold and bitcoin holdings.- total profit for 2023: $6.2B.- cash & cash equivalents cover now 90% of all issued tokens highest percentage in the last years.- total US T-bill exposure (direct + indirect): $80.3B.- excess equity: $5.4B (excess equity = undistributed profits on top of 100% reserves that Tether holds to back all issued tokens. Company decided to keep vast majority of profits within the stablecoin reserves to ensure highest resiliency).- excess equity > remaining secured loans ($5.4B vs $4.8B). In 2023 as promised Tether accumulated enough excess equity to remove the impact of secured loans on token reserves.- VC investments portfolio (outside of token reserves and consolidated report): $1.45B. Investments span across AI infrastructure Bitcoin mining P2P telecommunications and others. These are confirmed to remain outside of the consolidated reserves report within a new segregated VC umbrella so that such investments don’t and won’t have any impact on the token reserves.Any business that can do $2.85 billion in profit during a 90 day period is hard to ignore. This puts them on a $11.4 billion annual run rate in profit. As Bitwise CIO @Matt_Hougan pointed out Tether made more money than Goldman Sachs last quarter.Messari CEO @twobitidiot points out that Tether is now 10% of JP Morgan’s net profit but with way fewer employees.As I have pointed out before even if Tether has 100 employees than the company would be doing more than $100 million per employee in profit.That is the craziest statistic I have ever heard in business.$100000000+ in annual profit per employee.So much for those critics that continue to claim there are no problems solved with this new technology. The actual truth is that one of the most profitable businesses which is used by millions of people globally was built on top of the technology.Stablecoins including Tether USDC and others will continue to be very popular around the world as people look for a way to send stable value quickly and inexpensively. Anyone arguing the opposite is either unaware of the facts of the market or has an incentive to see progress happen slower.But markets don’t wait on anyone. And Tether is proving the critics wrong day-after-day. Maybe the naysayers will realize their error at some point. Just don’t count on it.

tweet_text: why switch off godi media a lesson from the recent past  hatewaves of horror how radio rwanda fueled the rwandan genocide  the rwandan genocide of 1994 a 100day nightmare that claimed over 800000 lives remains a stark reminder of humanitys darkest capabilities  while numerous factors intertwined to create this monstrous event the toxic role of hate mongering through radio particularly radio télévision libre des mille collines rtlm deserves our critical examination  from microphones to machetes   rtlm initially launched in 1993 as an entertainment source morphed into a weapon under the control of extremist hutu forces its airwaves became saturated with hate speech dehumanizing and demonizing the tutsi minority   tutsis were labelled cockroaches accomplices to a fabricated manipulating minds  the pervasiveness of radio in rwandan homes coupled with the emotionally charged language and relentless repetition of hateful messages created a toxic atmosphere   violence became normalized fear and anger festered and trust within communities evaporated this psychological warfare transformed ordinary citizens into willing participants in the genocide blurring the lines between bystander and perpetrator   beyond words a symphony of slaughter  rtlms influence transcended mere pronouncements it served as a communication hub for the hutu militia coordinating attacks and movements during the killing sprees  it pressured other media outlets to adopt its hateful narrative silencing dissent and creating a suffocating information monopoly  a legacy etched in blood  the rwandan genocide stands as a chilling testament to the medias immense power both for good and evil rtlms role in inciting mass murder served as a stark reminder of the dangers of unchecked hate speech   the international criminal tribunal for rwanda acknowledged this horrifying reality convicting key figures at rtlm yet the wounds of the genocide still fester in rwandan society  learning from the tweet_raw: Why Switch Off Godi Media(A Lesson From the Recent Past)Hatewaves of Horror: How Radio Rwanda Fueled the Rwandan GenocideThe Rwandan genocide of 1994 a 100-day nightmare that claimed over 800000 lives remains a stark reminder of humanitys darkest capabilities. While numerous factors intertwined to create this monstrous event the toxic role of hate mongering through radio particularly Radio Télévision Libre des Mille Collines (RTLM) deserves our critical examination.♦️From Microphones to Machetes RTLM initially launched in 1993 as an entertainment source morphed into a weapon under the control of extremist Hutu forces. Its airwaves became saturated with hate speech dehumanizing and demonizing the Tutsi minority. Tutsis were labelled cockroaches accomplices to a fabricated invasion and even targeted individuals were named their deaths encouraged with chilling pronouncements like go hunt them down!♦️The Psychological ArsenalRTLM wasnt just bombarding ears; it was manipulating Minds. The pervasiveness of radio in Rwandan homes coupled with the emotionally charged language and relentless repetition of hateful messages created a toxic atmosphere. Violence became normalized fear and anger festered and trust within communities evaporated. This psychological warfare transformed ordinary citizens into willing participants in the genocide blurring the lines between bystander and perpetrator. 👈📍Beyond Words a Symphony of SlaughterRTLMs influence transcended mere pronouncements. It served as a communication hub for the Hutu militia coordinating attacks and movements during the killing sprees. It pressured other media outlets to adopt its hateful narrative silencing dissent and creating a suffocating information monopoly.♦️A Legacy Etched in BloodThe Rwandan genocide stands as a chilling testament to the medias immense power both for good and evil. RTLMs role in inciting mass murder served as a stark reminder of the dangers of unchecked hate speech. The International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda acknowledged this horrifying reality convicting key figures at RTLM. Yet the wounds of the genocide still fester in Rwandan society.Learning from the AshesThe world has taken steps to prevent similar tragedies. The UN Plan of Action on the Safety of Journalists and the Responsibility of State Actors emphasizes protecting journalists and combating hate speech. However ongoing conflicts worldwide demonstrate the need for constant vigilance and action.Remembering the horrors of the Rwandan genocide and the role of RTLM isnt just about honoring the victims; its about preventing future atrocities. We must amplify responsible Journalism promote Media Literacy and hold perpetrators accountable. Open and critical dialogue is crucial in building a world where Media serves as a bridge not a weapon.#GodiMedia #ArrestSudhirChaudhary #ModiDisasterForIndia #BharatJodoNyayYatra

tweet_text: the cone nebula from hubble image credit hubble legacy archive nasa esa  processing  licence judy schmidt  explanation stars are forming in the gigantic dust pillar called the cone nebula cones pillars and majestic flowing shapes abound in stellar nurseries where natal clouds of gas and dust are buffeted by energetic winds from newborn stars the cone nebula a wellknown example lies within the bright galactic starforming region ngc 2264 the cone was captured in unprecedented detail in this closeup composite of several observations from the earthorbiting hubble space telescope while the cone nebula about 2500 lightyears away in monoceros is around 7 lightyears long the region pictured here surrounding the cones blunted head is a mere 25 lightyears across in our neck of the galaxy that distance is just over half way from our sun to its nearest stellar neighbors in the alpha centauri star system the massive star ngc 2264 irs seen by hubbles infrared camera in 1997 is the likely source of the wind sculpting the cone nebula and lies off the top of the image the cone nebulas reddish veil is produced by dust and glowing hydrogen gas
tweet_raw: The Cone Nebula from HubbleImage Credit: Hubble Legacy Archive NASA ESA - Processing & Licence: Judy SchmidtExplanation: Stars are forming in the gigantic dust pillar called the Cone Nebula. Cones pillars and majestic flowing shapes abound in stellar nurseries where natal clouds of gas and dust are buffeted by energetic winds from newborn stars. The Cone Nebula a well-known example lies within the bright galactic star-forming region NGC 2264. The Cone was captured in unprecedented detail in this close-up composite of several observations from the Earth-orbiting Hubble Space Telescope. While the Cone Nebula about 2500 light-years away in Monoceros is around 7 light-years long the region pictured here surrounding the cones blunted head is a mere 2.5 light-years across. In our neck of the galaxy that distance is just over half way from our Sun to its nearest stellar neighbors in the Alpha Centauri star system. The massive star NGC 2264 IRS seen by Hubbles infrared camera in 1997 is the likely source of the wind sculpting the Cone Nebula and lies off the top of the image. The Cone Nebulas reddish veil is produced by dust and glowing hydrogen gas.
